Day 18 (Thursday): Privacy by Design (Zero-PHI)
Hook: The biggest barrier to AI in clinical research is privacy.

Body: As an AI enthusiast, I know the power of these tools, but as a Senior CRA, I know the regulatory risks. One of the most common questions I get is: "How can I use an AI assistant without risking patient data?"

That’s why I designed CRABuddy with a strict, metadata-only architecture. I previously explored this with my project "CLARA," and I’ve carried those lessons forward. CRABuddy ensures zero storage of PHI, keeping you compliant with corporate and regulatory standards while still reaping the benefits of automation.

CTA: Get the benefits of AI with none of the compliance risk. [Link] Hashtags: #DataPrivacy #HIPAA #ClinicalTrials #CRABuddy

